If any FSP Participants and/or Friends of the FSP, especially NH natives, can come by and politely dispel any misinformation (if there is any) at the Democratic Party meeting announced it would be appreciated. -Todd
http://www.fosters.com/apps/pbcs.dll/article?AID=%2F20120220%2FGJNEWS_01%2F702209923&template=DoverRegion

The Dover Democratic Committee will meet Thursday, Feb. 23, at 7 p.m. at 660 Central Ave., at the Organizing for America office. The public is invited, and all Dover Democrats as well as undeclared voters are encouraged to come. 

Caitlin Rollo, chair of the Strafford County Democratic Committee, will speak on "The Free State Project in New Hampshire — Who? What? Where?" 

"It is crucial that Democrats learn about and understand the Free State Project, which has worked to recruit 20,000 people specifically to New Hampshire to further their political philosophy and agenda," the Dover committee chair Wendy Alley said in announcing the program.

Dover Democrats caucused on Feb. 4 to elect officers for 2012. Wendy Alley, the new chair, is an attorney with many years experience in politics and government. Other officers are Caroline French, vice chair; Bill Dudley, secretary; and Carole Appel, treasurer. Also elected were six ward chairs and six at-large delegates to the state Democratic Party Convention, which will be June 2. 

For more information about the Dover Democratic Committee and the February 23 meeting, call Alley at 742-1025.
